# SIEM Architecture

## Overview

The Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) infrastructure is designed to collect, process, analyze, and investigate security events generated within the SOC lab environment.

## Infrastructure

### KALI-ATTACKER

Role: Adversary Machine

IP Address: 192.168.44.131

Purpose:
Simulates attacker activity and generates security events.

### WS-01

Role: Victim Workstation

IP Address: 192.168.44.155

Purpose:
Generates endpoint telemetry and security logs.

### SPLUNK

Role: SIEM Server

Hostname: splunk

IP Address: 192.168.44.157

Operating System: Ubuntu 26.04 LTS

CPU: 2 Cores

Memory: 3.3 GB

Purpose:
Centralized log collection, detection engineering, incident investigation, and threat hunting.

## Data Flow

KALI-ATTACKER
↓
WS-01
↓
Sysmon
↓
Splunk Universal Forwarder
↓
Splunk Enterprise
↓
Detection Engineering
↓
Incident Investigation
↓
Threat Hunting

